Document: Your First 2D Game: Heads-Up Display
Path: godot/getting_started/first_2d_game/06.heads_up_display.rst
Summary: This section explains how to create a Heads-Up Display (HUD) in Godot to show game information like score and lives.

This tutorial section covers the creation of a Heads-Up Display (HUD) for your first 2D game in Godot. A HUD is essential for displaying important game information to the player, such as their score, remaining lives, or other relevant stats, without obstructing the main game view.

We will focus on setting up a separate scene for the HUD, which can then be instantiated and managed within your main game scene. This approach promotes modularity and makes it easier to update or modify the HUD independently.

Key steps typically involve:
*   Creating a new scene for the HUD.
*   Adding UI elements like Labels to display text.
*   Connecting signals from game logic to update the HUD.
*   Positioning the HUD elements appropriately on the screen.

By the end of this section, you will have a functional HUD displaying dynamic game information, enhancing the player's experience and providing crucial feedback during gameplay.
