Path: godot/getting_started/first_2d_game/06.heads_up_display.rst
Summary: This section explains how to connect the Heads Up Display (HUD) scene to the main game scene and update its functionality.

Connecting HUD to Main
Instance the HUD scene in Main. The scene tree should include the HUD node.

Connect the HUD's `start_game` signal to the `new_game()` function of the Main node.

In `new_game()`, update the score display and show the "Get Ready" message:
GDScript:
        $HUD.update_score(score)
        $HUD.show_message("Get Ready")
C#:
        var hud = GetNode<HUD>("HUD");
        hud.UpdateScore(_score);
        hud.ShowMessage("Get Ready!");

In `game_over()`, call the corresponding HUD function:
GDScript:
        $HUD.show_game_over()
C#:
        GetNode<HUD>("HUD").ShowGameOver();

In `_on_score_timer_timeout()`, keep the display in sync with the changing score:
GDScript:
        $HUD.update_score(score)
C#:
        GetNode<HUD>("HUD").UpdateScore(_score);

Warning: Remember to remove the call to `new_game()` from `_ready()` if you haven't already, otherwise your game will start automatically.
---CHUNK---
Document: First 2D Game Tutorial
Path: godot/getting_started/first_2d_game/06.heads_up_display.rst
Summary: This section explains how to use Godot's group feature to remove all mobs from the previous game when a new game starts.

To remove old creeps when starting a new game, you can use the group feature.
In the Mob scene, select the root node and go to the Groups tab.
Add a new group named "mobs".

Now all mobs will be in the "mobs" group.
To make all mobs disappear at the start of a new game, add the following line to the new_game() function in Main:

GDScript:
        get_tree().call_group("mobs", "queue_free")

C#:
        // Note that for calling Godot-provided methods with strings,
        // we have to use the original Godot snake_case name.
        GetTree().CallGroup("mobs", Node.MethodName.QueueFree);

The call_group() function calls the named function on every node in a group. In this case, it tells every mob to delete itself.

The game is mostly done at this point. The next part will cover adding a background, looping music, and keyboard shortcuts.